Federal Reserve Board Chairman PaulVolcker said international policymakers should make improvingthe stability of exchange rates a major priority.    In testimony before a Senate Banking subcommittee, Volckersaid he does not have any specific proposals for improvingexchange rate stability, but thought it was worthy goal.    "I do think we ought to be thinking about and working towardgreater exchange rate stability," Volcker said. "I think that theobjective of greater exchange rate stability ought to loomlarger among our various policy priorities." Reuter&#3;